# Preprocessing

This folder contains the preprocessing-related scripts and files used before running the paired and r75 benchmarks.

The preprocessing step prepares the PBMC RNA-ATAC multiome dataset for downstream integration analysis. The r75 missing-modality split was also prepared from the preprocessed paired dataset.

## Folder structure

```text
Preprocessing/
├── Preprocessed.py
├── Prepare_r75_data.py
└── r75_modality_status.csv
```

## Files

### `Preprocessed.py`

This script preprocesses the raw PBMC multiome dataset before integration analysis.

Main steps include:

- loading the raw 10x PBMC multiome dataset
- separating RNA and ATAC modalities
- applying quality control
- preprocessing RNA data
- preprocessing ATAC data
- saving the processed multiome object for downstream analysis

### `Prepare_r75_data.py`

This script prepares the r75 missing-modality setting from the preprocessed paired dataset.

In the r75 setting:

- 25% of cells remain paired
- 37.5% of cells are RNA-only
- 37.5% of cells are ATAC-only

### `r75_modality_status.csv`

This file records the modality status of each cell in the r75 benchmark.

Each cell is assigned to one of the following groups:

```text
paired
rna_only
atac_only
```

## Script-output summary

| Script | Main output |
|---|---|
| `Preprocessed.py` | Preprocessed PBMC multiome dataset used for downstream analysis |
| `Prepare_r75_data.py` | `r75_modality_status.csv` |

## Output usage

| Output | Used in |
|---|---|
| Preprocessed PBMC multiome dataset | `PAIRED_benchmark/` |
| `r75_modality_status.csv` | `r75_benchmark/` |

## Notes

- The paired benchmark used the complete preprocessed PBMC multiome dataset.
- The r75 benchmark was generated from the same preprocessed dataset.
- Cell-type annotation was performed downstream after integration.
- `r75_modality_status.csv` was used to identify whether each cell was paired, RNA-only or ATAC-only during the r75 benchmark.
